========
Software
========
Below is a list of software that is required for Populous.  The optional
software recommended for increased performance.

This is most likely an incomplete guide.  If you are using Debian you'll
see a list of packages that you need to have installed below.

Required
========

  * libxml2 (http://xmlsoft.org/downloads.html) (libxml2-dev)
  * libxslt (http://xmlsoft.org/downloads.html) (libxslt1-dev)
  * lxml >= 2.0.7 (http://codespeak.net/lxml/index.html)
  * ElementTree >= 1.3 (http://svn.effbot.org/public/elementtree-1.3/)

Optional
========

  * cjson >= 1.0.5
  * cElementTree >= 1.0.6 (http://svn.effbot.org/public/celementtree/)

Debian Install
==============

Here is a (mostly) complete list of Debian packages that are needed to run
Populous.

General::

    apt-get install build-essential libssl-dev xinetd openssl sysvconfig \
    rsync nfs-common ssh openssh-server python-flup python-imaging \
    python-markdown python-xapian python-cjson python-psycopg2 \
    python-docutils python-setuptools imagemagick wv libwv-dev memcached -y

Populous::

    apt-get install build-essential apache2-mpm-prefork python-imaging \
    python-markdown python-xapian python-cjson python-psycopg2 \
    python-docutils imagemagick wv libwv-dev memcached -y

AND

Python-memcached API:
    ftp://ftp.tummy.com/pub/python-memcached/python-memcached-1.43.tar.gz


Documentation
=============

To build the documentation you need the following:

  * Sphinx (http://sphinx.pocoo.org/)

For PDF output, you will need:

  * sudo apt-get install texlive-latex-extra
